  "prompt": "Do employees at Select Income REIT have a good work-life balance? Does this differ across positions and departments?",
  "response": "It's difficult to give a definitive \"yes\" or \"no\" answer about work-life balance at Select Income REIT (SIR) due to the following reasons:\n\n*   **SIR No Longer Exists:** Select Income REIT merged with Government Properties Income Trust in 2018 to form Office Properties Income Trust (OPI). Any information about the former company might not be relevant.\n*   **Limited Recent Employee Reviews:** Information about the old Select Income REIT's work environment and employee experiences are limited.\n\n**What General Factors Affect Work-Life Balance in Real Estate Companies?**\n\nHere are some general factors that influence work-life balance in real estate companies like the former SIR or current OPI:\n\n*   **Position Level:** Entry-level positions often have more structured hours than management roles. Higher-level positions may require more after-hours work to manage projects and responsibilities.\n*   **Department:**\n    *   **Property Management:** Property managers may need to be available for emergencies outside of regular hours, impacting work-life balance.\n    *   **Finance/Accounting:** Month-end and year-end closing periods can be very demanding, requiring longer hours.\n    *   **Acquisitions/Development:** These teams often work under tight deadlines to close deals or complete projects, leading to periods of intense work.\n    *   **Leasing:** Brokers and leasing agents may have to accommodate client schedules, which could include evenings and weekends.\n*   **Company Culture:** Some companies prioritize employee well-being and offer flexible work arrangements, while others have a more demanding culture.\n*   **Workload:** A heavy workload, regardless of the position or department, can negatively impact work-life balance.\n*   **Management Style:** Supportive and understanding managers can help employees manage their workload and prioritize their personal lives.\n\n**How to Find Information About Current Office Properties Income Trust (OPI) Work-Life Balance:**\n\n1.  **Glassdoor and Similar Sites:** Search for \"Office Properties Income Trust\" (OPI) on Glassdoor, Indeed, and similar websites. Read employee reviews specifically addressing work-life balance. Be aware that reviews can be subjective.\n2.  **LinkedIn:** Try to connect with current or former OPI employees on LinkedIn and ask about their experiences.\n3.  **Company Website/Careers Page:** Look for any information on OPI's website about employee benefits, wellness programs, or flexible work arrangements. These can be indicators of a company's commitment to work-life balance.\n4.  **Industry Networking:** If you know anyone in the commercial real estate industry, ask them if they have any insights into OPI's work environment.\n5.  **Interview Process (if applicable):** If you are interviewing for a position at OPI, ask specific questions about work-life balance during the interview. Inquire about typical hours, on-call requirements, and the company's policies on flexible work.\n\n**In conclusion, it is not possible to determine the work-life balance at the former Select Income REIT. The best way to get an idea of the current work-life balance at Office Properties Income Trust (OPI) is through current employee reviews and direct contact with employees.**",
